  "response_text": "When faced with an ambiguous sentence, I use a combination of natural language processing (NLP) techniques and linguistic rules to determine the most likely interpretation. Here's a step-by-step guide on how I decide which interpretation to favor:\n\n1. **Tokenization**: I break down the sentence into individual words or tokens. This helps me analyze each word's part of speech, grammatical function, and relationships with other words.\n2. **Part-of-speech tagging**: I identify the part of speech (noun, verb, adjective, adverb, etc.) for each token. This helps me understand the word's role in the sentence.\n3. **Dependency parsing**: I analyze the grammatical structure of the sentence by identifying the relationships between tokens, such as subject-verb-object relationships, modifiers, and clauses.\n4. **Semantic role labeling**: I identify the roles played by each token in the sentence, such as \"agent,\" \"patient,\" \"theme,\" or \"goal.\"\n5. **Context",
